[SN]TITLE[SN]
Paul Groves: Birmingham City appoint first-team coach

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Championship side Birmingham City have appointed Paul Groves as first-team coach on a 12-month rolling contract.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Former Bournemouth manager Groves joined Birmingham as part of manager Harry Redknapp's coaching team for the final three games of the season.
The 51-year-old had previously worked alongside Redknapp at Portsmouth between 2006 and 2008.
On 12 May, Redknapp signed a one-year deal to stay on as Birmingham boss after helping them avoid relegation.
